[[Image:Clam Lake ELF.jpg|thumb|225px|The U.S. Navy Clam Lake, Wisconsin [[Extremely low frequency|ELF]] transmitter in 1982.  Sections of the [[right of way (transportation)|rights of way]] for the power lines that make up the two crossed ground dipole antennas can be seen passing through the forest at lower left.  ]]

In [[radio communication]], a '''ground dipole''',<ref name="Barr">{{cite journal
